"__html":"Hyperthyroidism"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"c98801",
"children":[
"Hyperthyroidism"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_en_s10_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"88eb5a",
"children":[
"The term ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"thyrotoxicosis"
]
},
" encompasses any cause of thyroid hormone excess. ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Hyperthyroidism"
]
},
" is thyrotoxicosis caused by excessive endogenous thyroid hormone production."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"5e9a8f",
"children":[
"Look for symptoms of thyrotoxicosis:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"eec3ed",
"children":[
"nervousness, emotional lability"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"c4aa91",
"children":[
"increased sweating, heat intolerance"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"68dcf6",
"children":[
"palpitations"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"357dd4",
"children":[
"increased defecation"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"e4a22a",
"children":[
"weight loss"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"e4ea40",
"children":[
"menstrual irregularity"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"570a26",
"children":[
"Look for signs of thyrotoxicosis:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"a475c0",
"children":[
"tachycardia"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"0d3059",
"children":[
"lid lag"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"bcab49",
"children":[
"fine tremor"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"86d055",
"children":[
"muscle wasting, proximal muscle weakness"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"4a0bca",
"children":[
"hyperreflexia"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"b16621",
"children":[
"The most common causes of hyperthyroidism are Graves disease and toxic adenoma(s). Physical examination findings specific for Graves disease include goiter, ophthalmopathy (proptosis, chemosis, and extraocular muscle palsy), and pretibial myxedema."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"34686e",
"children":[
"Older adult patients with hyperthyroidism may present with depression, ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"atrial fibrillation",
"children":[
"AF"
]
},
","
]
},
" and ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"heart failure",
"children":[
"HF"
]
},
"."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f17310",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"Thyrotoxicosis occurs in destructive thyroiditis because thyroid damage results in release of preformed thyroid hormone into the circulation."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"24af68",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Thyroid storm"
]
},
" is the development of life-threatening hyperthyroidism associated with cardiac decompensation, fever, delirium, and psychosis. It may occur following surgery, infection, or administration of an acute iodine load (contrast agents) and may also develop in patients with untreated Graves disease. ",
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"Thyroid storm is a clinical diagnosis; no level of thyroid hormone elevation is diagnostic."
]
}
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_en_s10_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Testing"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"fa6a5a",
"children":[
"Testing"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"3f7e21",
"children":[
"Order serum ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"thyroid-stimulating hormone",
"children":[
"TSH"
]
},
" and free ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"free thyroxine",
"children":[
"T",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"4"
]
}
]
},
" levels to make the diagnosis of thyrotoxicosis. If TSH is suppressed but T",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"4"
]
},
" is normal, order free T",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"3"
]
},
" to diagnose T",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"3"
]
},
" toxicosis (rare)."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"87fa59",
"children":[
"Thyroglobulin levels can be elevated in hyperthyroidism and thyroiditis. ",
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"Intake of exogenous thyroid hormone suppresses thyroglobulin levels, which makes its measurement useful (when low) in patients with thyrotoxicosis caused by surreptitious use of thyroid hormone."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"989953",
"children":[
"An elevated serum ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"erythrocyte sedimentation rate",
"children":[
"ESR"
]
},
" supports thyroiditis, whereas TSH-receptor antibodies and thyroid-stimulating immunoglobulins are associated with Graves disease. However, antibodies need not be checked routinely in the evaluation of hyperthyroidism unless the diagnosis is unclear."
]
},
{
